{
  "_comment": [
    "Shared policy decision vectors - the single source of truth for lock-step",
    "between the Python LocalPolicyEngine and the Rego bundle (foundry.rego).",
    "tests/test_policy_parity.py runs every vector through LocalPolicyEngine;",
    "scripts/policy_parity.py runs the same vectors through `opa eval` in the OPA",
    "CI job. Both assert against `expected`, so the two engines cannot diverge",
    "silently (AGENTS.md invariant #2).",
    "",
    "Notes:",
    "- `reasons` and `required_approvals` are compared set-wise: Rego materialises",
    "  sets in sorted order while Python preserves insertion order, so only the",
    "  *set* of strings is load-bearing for audit parity.",
    "- Always set `risk.overall_risk` explicitly: the Python schema defaults it to",
    "  'medium' but absent-in-Rego would read as neither low nor medium.",
    "- `config.repo_confidence_threshold` (default 70) is injected into the OPA",
    "  input and passed to LocalPolicyEngine's constructor, proving the threshold",
    "  is threaded through rather than hardcoded.",
    "- `valid_action: false` marks an action outside the PolicyAction enum: Python",
    "  rejects it at the schema boundary (its form of default-deny) so only `allow`",
    "  is checked there; Rego's in-rule default-deny is checked in full."
  ],
  "vectors": [
    {
      "name": "low_risk_start_allows_draft_pr",
      "input": {
        "action": "start_agent",
        "ticket": {"work_type": "feature", "readiness": "ready"},
        "risk": {"overall_risk": "low"},
        "repo": {"name": "customer-web", "confidence": 90},
        "approval": {}
      },
      "expected": {
        "allow": true,
        "allowed_agent_mode": "draft_pr",
        "reasons": ["all minimum policy checks passed"],
        "required_approvals": []
      }
    },
